Paratopotypes. NMP
6 V
73810 / 1–3 , two adult males and an adult female, same locality and collecting data as holotype ; CBF 6052 , adult female, same locality and collecting data as holotype ;

Etymology. The specific name is a compound from the Latin castanea (Horse Chestnut,
Aesculus
) from which the Spanish castaña (vernacular name of the Brazil nut tree) was derived and the Latin col ō (to inhabit). The name is used as a noun in apposition and refers to the life history of the new species.
